<br>
To say that it was racist in any other way, is essentially saying that giving praise to a racist man in any way is in itself a racist comment, even when the comment isn't racially related.  If it Trent Lott's opinion (as it apparently is) that Thurmond would have placed the country into a better ecomical and defensive position than what resulted from the other candidate becoming president is not supporting racism.<br>
<br>
You're essentially stating that if Trent Lott had said any one of the following:<br>
