It would still have been a racist comment?<br>
<br>
It is VERY clear that for the comment to be racist that &quot;these problems&quot; must refer to racial issues.<br>
<br>
No, I can't find a Dem that started this, but you don't see me saying that it was the Democrats that started it.  On the other hand you are saying that it's the Republicans that had made this an issue.  Where is the republican that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>started</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> this?  Note, not looking for the first Republican to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>respond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the story.<br>
<br>
What is clear, is that its the press that is beating this drum.  Since they have the ear of the populace, the Republicans MUST respond to the crititism.  To sit there and ignore it would be foolish.  So to suggest that the Republican response is feeding this story is the wrong conclusion. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094" target="top">Wenin Huirunda</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
