Well if that's what you honestly believe, then there is no talking to you about this.  I believe for something to be racist, it must contain racist intentions.  No one can be an accidental racist.<br>
<br>
I suppose all that supported Clinton, believed that he couldn't have gotten any of his work done, without an intern sucking on his johnson in the Oval Office.  My point is that you can support a man, without supporting ALL of his actions and ideals.  Thurmond didn't come from no where, he was a politican before he ran for President.  So to suggest that Lott knew nothing of Thurmond's stance on other issues, or that Thurmond had no stance on other issues is ridiculous.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
